 de la Roche的兒子，於1305年出生在愛爾蘭庫迪 科克費爾莫易。他於1328年與Mrs. William Fleming在愛爾蘭庫迪 科克費爾莫易結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。"},"zh-hans":{"1305–":"1305年–殁","1305–Male":"1305年–殁","1310–Female":"1310年–殁","1328–1350":"1328年–1350年","–1329":"–1329年","1305":"1305年","1310":"1310年","1350":"1350年","1329":"1329年","1328":"1328年","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"爱尔兰庫迪 科克費爾莫易","lifeSummary":"William Fleming是Jacqueline de la Roche的儿子，于1305年出生在爱尔兰庫迪 科克費爾莫易。他于1328年与Mrs. William Fleming在爱尔兰庫迪 科克費爾莫易结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。"},"hr":{"1305–":"1305.–preminuo","1305–Male":"1305.–preminuo","1310–Female":"1310–preminula","1328–1350":"1328.–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305.","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328.","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irska"},"cs":{"1305–":"1305–Zesnulý","1305–Male":"1305–Zesnulý","1310–Female":"1310–Zesnulá","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irsko"},"da":{"1305–":"1305–Afdød","1305–Male":"1305–Afdød","1310–Female":"1310–Afdød","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irland"},"nl":{"1305–":"1305–Overleden","1305–Male":"1305–Overleden","1310–Female":"1310–Overleden","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Ierland"},"en":{"1305–":"1305–Deceased","1305–Male":"1305–Deceased","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fleming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Fleming was born in 1305, in Fermoy, County Cork, Ireland as the son of Jacqueline de la Roche. He married Mrs. William Fleming in 1328, in Fermoy, County Cork, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1305–":"1305–Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1305–":"1305–Kuollut","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irlanti"},"fr":{"1305–":"1305–Décédé","1305–Male":"1305–Décédé","1310–Female":"1310–Décédée","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irlande","lifeSummary":"William Fleming est né en 1305, à Fermoy, County Cork, Irlande, fils de Jacqueline de la Roche. Il a épousé Mrs. William Fleming en 1328, à Fermoy, County Cork, Irlande. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1305–":"1305–Verstorben","1305–Male":"1305–Verstorben","1310–Female":"1310–Verstorben","1328–1350":"1328–1350","–1329":"–1329","1305":"1305","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1329":"1329","1328":"1328","Fermoy, Cork, Munster, Ireland":"Fermoy, County Cork, Irland","lifeSummary":"William Fleming wurde 1305 in Fermoy, County Cork, Irland, als Sohn von Jacqueline de la Roche geboren. Er hat 1328 in Fermoy, County Cork, Irland Mrs. William Fleming geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1305–":